      "body" : "@Jesper You says they are 100% the same thing and on the next sentence you point out the difference! They are not the same. The fact that two methods exist is a clear indicator of this. exists() will return true if the file exists. It will return false if it does not exist or it can&#39;t tell. The notExists() method will return true if the file does exists. It will return false if it exists or it can&#39;t tell."
